      {
        "type": "email",
        "html": "<p>After pretending to be powerless in the face of the Ohio derailment disaster, on Tuesday Transportation Secretary Pete Buttigieg promised to crack down on trains transporting hazardous materials. <strong><a href=\"__GHOST_URL__/buttigieg-pressured-into-promising-to-do-his-job/?utm_source=newsletter-email&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=newsletter-article\">Our featured story today</a></strong> explores Pete’s turnaround — and how our coverage of lax rail regulations helped deliver the change.</p>"
